bug.short_desc: [Automation][Regression] Drill through to document will display html with page break effect [0301]

long_desc.thetext:
Description: Drill through to document will display html with page break effect. Regression of #149615
Build number: 2.3.0.v20080104-0800
Steps to reproduce: 1. new a report with two items, set page break between them 2. new a report, define drill through link to report document of first report 3. preview in Layout and click the drill through link
Expected result: Target report should display html format without page break effect because page break in hidden in html format.
Actual result: Target report displayed page break effect in html.
Is this NOT a bug? What is the reason page break should be ignored in html format?
Engine has a flag named "HTMLPagination" to define pagination. Now when call render task, the HTMLPagination value is forced to true. We can't set it to false. Need do more discuess..
For "Select a format for target report", choose HTML. Preview and click the link, the report will be opened in Web Viewer with page break effect.

Fixed it.
Add a HTMLPagination choice in the hyperlink parameter builder.
